    "comment": "Edge: HPCA -> AP-2 complex | Relation: causally upstream of, positive effect | PMID: 16055064 | Model: rat/hippocampal neurons, rat/hippocampal slices | Perturbation: KD (antisense oligonucleotides), mut (Ca²⁺-binding mutant) | Assay: co-immunoprecipitation, whole-cell patch clamp (LTD recording) | Fig: Palmer 2005 | Note: Hippocalcin forms a Ca²⁺-dependent complex with AP2 and GluA2, bridging Ca²⁺ signaling to AMPAR cargo recognition at endocytic sites. Hippocalcin knockdown blocks hippocampal LTD, indicating it is required for activity-dependent AMPAR recruitment to clathrin-coated pits.",
